I bought the paper study guides as well as all 3 android study guides from asa. I ended up going to a prep school in nashville. The asa studyware is a waste of time, they do not have the full faa test bank and test mode is not an acurrate depiction of what you will see on the real test. If your going to study 2600 questions you want them to be the real questions you will see on the test. Ive been here one week and have passed all 3 tests and am now studying the o&p. I just wish i could get my money back from asa.

For 5 bucks you cant go wrong.only issue I have is that this app does not have all the FAA test bank questions. I encountered 4 new never before seen questions,same with the general app. But, if your happy just getting a high score this will get you there. I know im picky but I was shootin for 100%, I scored 100 on the general but was lucky with the new questions,i missed 1 on the airframe ,and I still believe my answer was best choice,but FAA answer was different. Focus on 1 test per week with these apps and you should ace them with no problem.
